@startuml
!theme plain
title Help with COVID - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor "User" as User
participant "Next.js Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Nav Component" as Nav
participant "AddressInput" as AddressInput
participant "Google Maps API" as GoogleMaps
participant "FirebaseAuth" as Auth
participant "Firebase Functions\n(Express)" as Functions
participant "API Routes" as APIRoutes
participant "Onfleet Service" as Onfleet
participant "Sendgrid Service" as Sendgrid
participant "Twilio Service" as Twilio
participant "Firebase Firestore" as Firestore
participant "Firebase Auth" as FirebaseAuth

== User Authentication Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Access application
Frontend -> Nav: Render navigation
Frontend -> Auth: Check authentication status
Auth -> FirebaseAuth: Validate user session
FirebaseAuth --> Auth: Return auth state
Auth --> Frontend: Authentication result

User -> Frontend: Click login/signup
Frontend -> APIRoutes: POST /api/login
APIRoutes -> FirebaseAuth: Authenticate with Firebase token
FirebaseAuth --> APIRoutes: Auth token
APIRoutes -> APIRoutes: Create cookie session
APIRoutes --> Frontend: Set session cookie
Frontend --> User: Redirect to authenticated page

== Volunteer Signup Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Navigate to /offer-help
Frontend -> Frontend: Render OfferHelp component
User -> Frontend: Fill volunteer form
User -> AddressInput: Enter address
AddressInput -> GoogleMaps: Request address autocomplete
GoogleMaps --> AddressInput: Return address suggestions
AddressInput --> User: Display suggestions
User -> AddressInput: Select address

User -> Frontend: Submit volunteer form
Frontend -> Functions: POST /tasks/workers (create worker)
Functions -> Onfleet: Create worker via API
Onfleet --> Functions: Worker created response
Functions -> Sendgrid: Add email to mailing list
Sendgrid --> Functions: Email added confirmation
Functions -> Firestore: Store volunteer data
Firestore --> Functions: Data stored
Functions --> Frontend: Success response
Frontend -> Frontend: Render VolunteerConfirmation
Frontend --> User: Show confirmation message

== Request Help Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Navigate to /request-help
Frontend -> Frontend: Render RequestHelp component
Frontend --> User: Display instructions
User -> User: Contact via phone/email
User -> Functions: Submit help request (external channel)
Functions -> Twilio: Verify phone/zipcode
Twilio --> Functions: Verification result
Functions -> Onfleet: Create task
Onfleet --> Functions: Task created
Functions -> Firestore: Create team if needed
Firestore --> Functions: Team created/retrieved
Functions -> Onfleet: Assign task to team
Onfleet --> Functions: Task assigned
Functions --> User: Confirmation

== Task Management Flow ==
Functions -> Onfleet: GET /tasks (retrieve tasks)
Onfleet --> Functions: Task list
Functions -> Functions: Process task data
Functions --> Frontend: Return tasks

Frontend -> Functions: PUT /tasks/:id (update task)
Functions -> Onfleet: Update task via API
Onfleet --> Functions: Task updated
Functions -> Firestore: Update task metadata
Firestore --> Functions: Metadata updated
Functions --> Frontend: Update confirmation

Frontend -> Functions: DELETE /tasks/:id
Functions -> Onfleet: Delete task via API
Onfleet --> Functions: Task deleted
Functions --> Frontend: Deletion confirmation

== Team Management Flow ==
Frontend -> Functions: POST /teams (create team)
Functions -> Firestore: Create team document
Firestore --> Functions: Team created
Functions --> Frontend: Team data

Frontend -> Functions: GET /teams (list teams)
Functions -> Firestore: Query teams
Firestore --> Functions: Teams list
Functions --> Frontend: Return teams

Frontend -> Functions: PUT /teams/:id (update team)
Functions -> Firestore: Update team document
Firestore --> Functions: Team updated
Functions --> Frontend: Update confirmation

Frontend -> Functions: DELETE /teams/:id
Functions -> Firestore: Delete team document
Firestore --> Functions: Team deleted
Functions --> Frontend: Deletion confirmation

== Worker Management Flow ==
Frontend -> Functions: GET /workers (list workers)
Functions -> Onfleet: Retrieve workers via API
Onfleet --> Functions: Workers list
Functions --> Frontend: Return workers

Frontend -> Functions: PUT /workers/:id (update worker)
Functions -> Onfleet: Update worker via API
Onfleet --> Functions: Worker updated
Functions --> Frontend: Update confirmation

Frontend -> Functions: DELETE /workers/:id
Functions -> Onfleet: Delete worker via API
Onfleet --> Functions: Worker deleted
Functions -> Sendgrid: Remove from mailing list
Sendgrid --> Functions: Removed confirmation
Functions --> Frontend: Deletion confirmation

== Logout Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Click logout
Frontend -> APIRoutes: POST /api/logout
APIRoutes -> APIRoutes: Clear session cookie
APIRoutes --> Frontend: Logout success
Frontend -> Auth: Clear auth state
Frontend --> User: Redirect to homepage

@enduml
